data.description: Under contract-accepting backup offers. ***This home received no water damage or any other type of damage from the recent Hurricane Idalia*** Very Attractively Repriced! Nestled within the sought-after Riviera Bay neighborhood of St. Petersburg, this inviting 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom home offers 1,618 square feet of comfortable living space. Inside, you'll find granite countertops gracing the kitchen and bathrooms, adding a touch of luxury to your daily life. The large bay window in the front of the home and the double sliding door in the rear, leading to the spacious backyard, provides an abundance of sunlight. The split bedroom layout ensures privacy, making this home a perfect choice for families or those seeking a bit of solitude. Step outside into your private oasis, where entertaining is a breeze. The backyard boasts a covered deck, perfect for hosting gatherings and enjoying the amazing Florida weather. An above-ground pool adds a perfect refreshing touch for those sunny days. For those with a green thumb, you'll appreciate the additional features this property offers - a shed for storage and a small garden where you can nurture your favorite plants and flowers. But there's more to this community than meets the eye. Riviera Bay is known for its tight-knit neighborhood spirit, where residents come together for holiday events and celebrations throughout the year. It's not just a home; it's a welcoming community that feels like family. Conveniently situated near major highways, this home provides quick access to Tampa Airport, downtown St. Petersburg, and downtown Tampa. Boating enthusiasts will appreciate the community boat ramp just down the street, granting access to picturesque canals, Riviera Bay, Tampa Bay, and the Gulf. This home offers not just comfort and charm but also a wonderful opportunity for those looking to begin their Florida homeownership journey. Act quickly so you don't miss out on this opportunity to own a piece of Riviera Bay. The seller's flood insurance policy is transferable. Don't let this gem slip away!
